prompt: Summarize the following story in first person: What a busy day at work today! I'm exhausted but in a good way. It's been a whirlwind since starting this job about a month and a half ago but it's worth it. Honestly, I can't believe that I'm here. I never imagined that I'd be working for a company such as this. Thank god for Prof. J (which reminds me..purchase birthday card for Prof. J). I don't know if I would of pass her class and did so well on the certification exam two months ago without her encouragement.  It was a tough ride. I can't believe I'm here now. I remember the night before taking my exam, I barely slept, I was so nervous. When Prof. J told me that I had done so well on my exam, I couldn't believe it. What a moment.

choices.text: She gave me a hug and said "you deserve it" I felt like I had just won an Oscar. Now, I'm working for a big company and making good money. My friends are all so jealous. I'm just grateful that I have this opportunity. It's been a wild ride but I'm glad I'm here.
